questions.question: What is your height in inch/cm?
info: Your height is one of the measurements which will help us determine your nutritional requirements

questions.question: What is your current weight in kg/lbs?
info: This is a vital parameter to help us understand your nutritional requirements.  Abnormal body weight and variations can be indicative of various health risks.

For an accurate weight measurement, it's best to weigh yourself in the morning, before breakfast and after you empty your bowels.  It's best to always weigh yourself at the same time.  Please refer to the 3D Illustration for further help.

info: It is essential for us to understand the reason behind your weight change before advising you on a new health regimen
Think of a reason that might lead to this weight change
Change in your calorie intake will have a direct impact on your weight
Recall any changes to your diet, such as new types of food, eating out more frequently, or increasing your salt intake.  Any changes to your regular eating habits can change your calorie intake.

questions.option: My levels of physical activity have changed
info: Any changes in your energy output levels can lead to weight change
Pay attention to any changes to your normal physical routine

questions.option: I have started taking new medication
info: Some medication can lead to weight changes
Medication like corticosteroids, anti-depressants, diabetic medication, anti-hypersensitive, contraceptives, antihistamines, anticonvulsants and mood stabilizers can cause weight change.
Hormones can affect the body's metabolism, so any hormonal changes can affect your weight
If there are no changes in the lifestyle of food consumption, hormones could be responsible for weight changes

snippets.msg: Breakfast is the most important meal of the day as it breaks the overnight fast.  You're on the right track, tell us a bit more about your breakfast.

Thank you for letting us know, this information is important.  You may already know that breakfast is the most important meal of the day, as it breaks the overnight fast.  Skipping breakfast can lead to slower metabolism, increases stress levels, increased risk of heart disease and even weight gain.  Let us know a bit more about your breakfast.

snippets.msg: Snacking isn't bad, just choose wisely!  Making the wrong choice can mean unnecessary calories which add extra kilograms to your weight.  Unhealthy snacks can also increase your cholesterol, cause tooth decay, and increase the risk of diabetes.
